  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      ALS is a severe progressive neurodegenerative disease characterized by degeneration motor
      neurons leading to death in 3 to 5 years. Gradually in time, the patient deprived of all
      motor skills as well as the possibility of communication written and oral developing a state
      close Locked In Syndrome (LIS). The main objective is to establish the feasibility of
      brain-computer interface using the pathological condition, with dependent disabled subjects
      as a means of communication.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
